title: For Sale:  WTS/WTT Eddystone M1917 Enfield
postcontent: "US Rifle, Caliber .30, Model of 1917"The M1917 Enfield, although not being nearly as well-known as the Springfield M1903, was the standard-issue rifle for all American Expeditionary Forces in Europe and were infact produced and issued in significantly greater numbers than the Springfield M1903. It was directly derived from the British pattern P14 enfield, which was chambered in .303 British. An interesting result of the conversion process to .30-06 caliber meant that the internal magazine can actually hold 6 rounds, instead of 5 such as is supplied by stripper clips or the M1903 springfield internal magazine.This rifle was built at Eddystone Arsenal in April 1918, which definitely would have seen use with the AEF with 7 months remaining in WWI after manufacturing date.Refurbished in WWII with the typical USMC (flaming bomb) bolt and JA barrel. Despite the military's general phasing-out of the P17 Enfield after WWI, there were still many confirmed reports of its use in WWII as well; primarily stateside for training (due to a shortage of M1 Garand's) but also to some artillery units and rear-echelon troops. This rifle's refurbishment suggests that it indeed served one of those purposes.This rifle has been pressure tested as of November 2016 and checked by multiple gunsmiths to verify its very good condition. It is fully functional and cycles and fires fantastically.The rifle, reproduction leather sling, and 10 stripper clips will be included.This rifle is being sold as-is, with no warranty implied or given. As such, I will not ship this rifle and will only meet face-to-face, so you can verify functionality of the action.Cash is king, but I will entertain all reasonable offers. I primarily enjoy rifles and unique firearms.
